Swarm mode: autonomous-development
Objective: Implement tool call tracking for swarm agents.

Read the full spec at docs/superpowers/specs/2026-03-15-tool-call-tracking-design.md before starting.

Implementation priorities (in order):

1. DB TABLES: In db.py, add tool_calls and mcp_status tables with CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS migrations. Add methods: record_tool_call(), get_tool_usage(), get_tool_failure_summary(), record_mcp_status(), get_mcp_status(). All use existing conn pattern.

2. STREAM-JSON PARSING: In swarm/controller.py, add _parse_stream_event() method that handles init (MCP status), assistant (tool_use start), user (tool_result completion), and result (final text) events. Track pending tool uses with timestamps for duration calculation. Extract MCP server name from tool names (mcp__server__tool -> server).

3. REWRITE _stream_agent_output: Switch from text line parsing to JSON line parsing. Each stdout line is a JSON object. Parse with _parse_stream_event(). Still write raw lines to trace files. Store tool calls in self._agent_tool_calls dict. Add self._agent_final_results dict for stream-json result text.

4. SWITCH OUTPUT FORMAT: Change build_claude_cmd call in _spawn_agent() to pass output_format="stream-json". Update monitor_agents() to extract AD_RESULT from self._agent_final_results first, falling back to self._agent_outputs.

5. PLANNER VISIBILITY: In swarm/context.py, add _render_tool_failures() and _render_mcp_status() methods. Include in build_state() so the planner sees tool failures and broken MCP servers in its state text.

6. CLI COMMAND: In cli.py, add autodev tool-usage command with --run-id, --failures-only, --top flags. Shows tool usage summary from DB.

7. TESTS: test_tool_tracking.py covering stream event parsing (init, tool_use, tool_result, result, invalid JSON), DB methods (record, query, summary), MCP status capture, AD_RESULT extraction from stream-json. All existing tests must pass.

Use .venv/bin/python for all Python commands.
Run .venv/bin/python -m pytest tests/ -q to verify changes.
Run .venv/bin/ruff check src/ tests/ to verify linting.
Run .venv/bin/bandit -r src/ -lll -q to verify security.

